cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper analyzes a two-tier heterogeneous cellular network and focuses on the performance benefits of uplink/downlink decoupling. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the spectral and energy efficiency of the system, which is a key aspect of information theory.
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of a communication network, which is the primary focus of this sub-category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the system performance and efficiency, which is a key aspect of systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not the primary focus, the paper does mention the joint improvement of spectral and energy efficiency, which is important for multimedia applications.
